      "id": "5c01853c_6d83fe21",
      "file_path": "build/creating_data/download-files.sh",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 26,
      "message": "This is from the time of our onap bash installer, when scripts have been used separately and concatenated together in one big selfinstaller, there it was necessary to not source the same files again. Here it is not necessary if there is no intention to splice all scripts to one. It is the same logic as with header files in C when you use similar guards with macro define. Other reason was to correctly set SCRIPT_DIR and LOCAL_PATH which may or may not be needed since the common-functions is removed of all the old functions and code",
